lead_paragraph: About 900 jubilant fans and employees of the Thai billionaire who owns Leicester City roared when the final whistle blew in their team's 1-1 draw at Manchester United on Sunday that left them on the brink of winning the Premier League title.

headline.print_headline: Party Time in Bangkok as Leicester Inch Closer to Title
headline.main: Party Time in Bangkok as Leicester Inch Closer to Title
